<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="8" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis box="[849,966,672,695]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="8">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
The new species is fairly close to 
<taxonomicName authority="Peckham, Peckham &amp; Wheeler, 1889" authorityName="Peckham, Peckham &amp; Wheeler" authorityYear="1889" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Lyssomanes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antillanus">
<emphasis box="[822,1076,704,727]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="8">Lyssomanes antillanus</emphasis>
Peckham, Peckham &amp; Wheeler, 1889
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Petrunkevitch, 1933" authorityName="Petrunkevitch" authorityYear="1933" box="[895,1318,736,759]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Lyssomanes" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="portoricensis">
<emphasis box="[895,1072,736,759]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="8">L. portoricensis</emphasis>
Petrunkevitch, 1933
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Taczanowski, 1872" authorityName="Taczanowski" authorityYear="1872" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Lyssomanes" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unicolor">
<emphasis box="[1334,1461,736,759]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="8">L. unicolor</emphasis>
(Taczanowski, 1872)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Brignoli, 1984" authorityName="Brignoli" authorityYear="1984" box="[1122,1408,768,791]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Lyssomanes" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="michae">
<emphasis box="[1122,1235,768,791]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="8">L. michae</emphasis>
Brignoli, 1984
</taxonomicName>
(see Galiano, 1962: pl. III, figs. 8–9 and pl. VI, figs. 1–3; Galiano, 1980: pl. III, figs. 23–24; Brignoli, 1984: figs. 4, 7), but can be easily distinguished from them by the elongated and almost touching embolus and median apophysis (clearly separated in the above species), as well as by the ribbon-shaped conductor (fan-shaped in the above species) (see 
<figureCitation box="[1089,1196,991,1015]" captionStart="Figs. 1 – 4" captionStartId="0.[120,162,2054,2072]" captionTargetBox="[288,1287,1223,2031]" captionTargetId="figure@0.[284,1295,1218,2038]" captionTargetPageId="0" captionText="Figs. 1 – 4: Male palp of Lyssomanes romani sp. n. (holotype). 1 Mesal view; 2 Ventral view; 3 Ectal view; 4 Embolic division, dorsal view. Scale lines = 0.2 mm." pageId="0" pageNumber="8">Figs. 1–4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
